{
  "texts": [
    "In what follows I and J represent bases of p-sites a and b respectively.",
    "Intuitively base J succeeds to base I, J being the result of the recomposition of I through φ.",
    "We interpret f (i) = j as the fact that i contributes to the emergence of j.",
    "If f -1 (j) = {i 1,..., i p } we interpret j as a new political entity or party that is the result of the union or merger of i 1,..., i p, its parents.",
    "In order that this recomposition be simplicial the function φ has to satisfy structural conditions that make it a map of domain the p-site a and codomain the p-site b."
  ]
}